Can we create objects in Java without constructor ?
Ans - No, we always need a constructor. Even if we dont add a constructor, Java will.

Can we create objects in Java without defining constructor ?
Ans - Yes, if we dont define any constructor, java will add default constructor.

Do we have access modifiers for constructors ?
Ans - Yes, all access modifiers are applicable to constructors.

if we add a constructor, java will not provide default constructor


2 or more  variables holding  the same object reference is called sallow copy
S s1=new S();
s2=s1

2 or more variables holding different object reference but same values is called deep copy
S s1=new S();
S s2=new S(s1);

